<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/blog-detail.css">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Header - Simplified without navigation -->
    <header class="site-header">
        <div class="left-header">
            <a href="/" class="header-text">INTERIOR DESIGN &<br>ARCHITECTURE STUDIO</a>
        </div>
        <div class="center-header">
            <a href="/" class="logo">
                <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Studio Logo" class="logo-img">
            </a>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Hero Section - Black Background -->
    <section class="blog-hero">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <div class="blog-meta">
                <span class="blog-category"><%= blog.category %></span>
                <span class="blog-date"><%= blog.date %></span>
            </div>
            <h1 class="blog-title"><%= blog.title %></h1>
            <p class="blog-subtitle"><%= blog.subtitle %></p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image">
            <div class="parallax-image" style="background-image: url('<%= blog.heroImage %>');"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Blog Content - Creamy Brown Background -->
    <article class="blog-content">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
            <div class="main-content">
                <p class="lead-paragraph">In the realm of interior design, creating spaces that transcend fleeting trends while embracing contemporary sensibilities is an art form that requires a deep understanding of both classical principles and modern aesthetics.</p>
                
                <h2>The Foundation of Timeless Design</h2>
                <p>At its core, timeless design is rooted in principles that have endured through centuries of architectural and design evolution. The careful consideration of proportion, scale, and harmony forms the foundation upon which all enduring spaces are built.</p>
                
                <div class="image-block">
                    <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[0] %>" alt="Elegant interior showing timeless design principles">
                    <span class="image-caption">Classical proportions meet contemporary materials in this London residence</span>
                </div>

                <h2>Material Selection and Craftsmanship</h2>
                <p>The selection of materials plays a crucial role in creating spaces that age gracefully. Natural materials like stone, wood, and metal not only provide durability but also develop character over time, adding layers of history to the space.</p>

                <blockquote>
                    "True luxury lies not in opulence, but in the perfect execution of simplicity."
                </blockquote>

                <div class="dual-image-block">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[1] %>" alt="Material detail">
                        <span class="image-caption">Hand-finished brass details</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[2] %>" alt="Craftsmanship detail">
                        <span class="image-caption">Custom joinery work</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>The Role of Light and Space</h2>
                <p>Natural light is perhaps the most fundamental element in creating timeless interiors. The way light interacts with space throughout the day brings life and movement to even the most minimal designs.</p>
                
                <!-- New Section 1 - Color Theory -->
                <h2>The Psychology of Color in Interior Design</h2>
                <p>Color has the power to transform a space, evoke emotions, and create specific atmospheres. Understanding color theory is essential for creating harmonious interiors that resonate with their inhabitants.</p>
                
                <div class="image-block">
                    <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[3] || 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1616486338812-3dadae4b4ace?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80' %>" alt="Color theory in interior design">
                    <span class="image-caption">A carefully curated color palette creates a cohesive and inviting atmosphere</span>
                </div>
                
                <p>The color wheel serves as a fundamental tool for designers, helping to identify complementary, analogous, and triadic color schemes. Each color carries its own psychological weight—blues promote calm and productivity, greens connect us to nature, while warm tones like red and orange stimulate energy and conversation.</p>
                
                <!-- New Section 2 - Sustainability -->
                <h2>Sustainable Design: The Future of Interior Architecture</h2>
                <p>As environmental consciousness grows, sustainable design has moved from a trend to a necessity. The integration of eco-friendly materials, energy-efficient systems, and waste-reducing practices is reshaping the industry.</p>
                
                <div class="dual-image-block">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[4] || 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600607687939-ce8a6c25118c?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80' %>" alt="Sustainable materials">
                        <span class="image-caption">Reclaimed wood adds character and sustainability</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[5] || 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600585154340-be6161a56a0c?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80' %>" alt="Energy-efficient design">
                        <span class="image-caption">Natural lighting reduces energy consumption</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <p>Sustainable design isn't just about using recycled materials—it's about creating spaces that minimize environmental impact throughout their lifecycle. This includes selecting locally sourced materials to reduce transportation emissions, incorporating passive design principles to reduce energy needs, and choosing finishes that don't off-gas harmful chemicals.</p>
                
                <!-- New Section 3 - Technology Integration -->
                <h2>The Intersection of Technology and Interior Design</h2>
                <p>Smart homes and integrated technology are revolutionizing how we interact with our living spaces. The challenge for designers is to seamlessly incorporate these innovations without compromising aesthetic integrity.</p>
                
                <div class="image-block">
                    <img src="<%= blog.contentImages[6] || 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558002038-1055907df827?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80' %>" alt="Smart home technology">
                    <span class="image-caption">Discreetly integrated technology enhances functionality without compromising design</span>
                </div>
                
                <p>From voice-controlled lighting systems to hidden charging stations and automated climate control, technology is becoming an invisible yet essential element of modern interiors. The key is to design with technology in mind from the beginning, ensuring that wires, sensors, and control panels are thoughtfully concealed while remaining accessible.</p>
                
                <blockquote>
                    "The best technology is the one you don't notice—it simply works, enhancing your life without demanding attention."
                </blockquote>
            </div>

            <aside class="sidebar">
                <div class="author-info">
                    <img src="<%= blog.author.image %>" alt="<%= blog.author.name %>" class="author-image">
                    <h3><%= blog.author.name %></h3>
                    <p><%= blog.author.role %></p>
                </div>
                <div class="related-posts">
                    <h4>Related Articles</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <% blog.relatedPosts.forEach(function(post) { %>
                            <li><a href="<%= post.link %>"><%= post.title %></a></li>
                        <% }); %>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </aside>
        </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Next Article Section - Black Background -->
    <section class="next-article">
        <div class="next-article-content">
            <span class="next-label">NEXT ARTICLE</span>
            <h2><%= blog.nextArticle.title %></h2>
            <a href="<%= blog.nextArticle.link %>" class="read-more">Read Article</a>
        </div>
        <div class="next-article-image">
            <div class="parallax-image" style="background-image: url('<%= blog.nextArticle.image %>');"></div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Contact Section - Creamy Brown Background -->
    <section class="contact-section">
        <div class="contact-wrapper">
            <div class="contact-content">
                <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
                <p class="contact-intro">Interested in transforming your space? We'd love to hear from you. Our team of experienced designers is ready to bring your vision to life.</p>
                
                <div class="contact-info">
                    <div class="contact-item">
                        <h3>Studio Location</h3>
                        <p>123 Design Avenue<br>London, UK SW1A 1AA</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="contact-item">
                        <h3>Contact Details</h3>
                        <p>Email: info@interiordesignstudio.com<br>Phone: +44 20 1234 5678</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="contact-item">
                        <h3>Follow Us</h3>
                        <div class="social-links">
                            <a href="#" class="social-link">Instagram</a>
                            <a href="#" class="social-link">Pinterest</a>
                            <a href="#" class="social-link">LinkedIn</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <form class="contact-form">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="name">Name</label>
                        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="email">Email</label>
                        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="message">Message</label>
                        <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" required></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Send Message</button>
                </form>
            </div>
            <div class="contact-image">
                <div class="parallax-image" data-image="<%= blog.contentImages[10] || 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1618221195710-dd6b41faaea6?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80' %>"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Scripts -->
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.11.5/gsap.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.11.5/ScrollTrigger.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/studio-freight/lenis@1.0.19/bundled/lenis.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/javascripts/blog-detail.js"></script>
    <script>
        // Initialize GSAP ScrollTrigger
        gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

        // Set background images from data attributes
        document.querySelectorAll('.parallax-image[data-image]').forEach(element => {
            const imageUrl = element.getAttribute('data-image');
            element.style.backgroundImage = `url('${imageUrl}')`;
        });

        // Parallax effect for hero image
        const heroImage = document.querySelector('.hero-image .parallax-image');
        if (heroImage) {
            gsap.to(heroImage, {
                yPercent: -20,
                ease: "power1.inOut",
                scrollTrigger: {
                    trigger: '.blog-hero',
                    start: 'top top',
                    end: 'bottom top',
                    scrub: 0.5,
                    markers: false
                }
            });
        }

        // Parallax effect for content images
        const contentImages = document.querySelectorAll('.image-block .parallax-image, .dual-image-block .parallax-image');
        contentImages.forEach((image, index) => {
            gsap.to(image, {
                yPercent: -15,
                ease: "power1.inOut",
                scrollTrigger: {
                    trigger: image.parentElement,
                    start: 'top bottom',
                    end: 'bottom top',
                    scrub: 0.5,
                    markers: false
                }
            });
        });

        // Parallax effect for next article image
        const nextArticleImage = document.querySelector('.next-article-image .parallax-image');
        if (nextArticleImage) {
            gsap.to(nextArticleImage, {
                yPercent: -20,
                ease: "power1.inOut",
                scrollTrigger: {
                    trigger: '.next-article',
                    start: 'top bottom',
                    end: 'bottom top',
                    scrub: 0.5,
                    markers: false
                }
            });
        }

        // Parallax effect for contact image
        const contactImage = document.querySelector('.contact-image .parallax-image');
        if (contactImage) {
            gsap.to(contactImage, {
                yPercent: -15,
                ease: "power1.inOut",
                scrollTrigger: {
                    trigger: '.contact-section',
                    start: 'top bottom',
                    end: 'bottom top',
                    scrub: 0.5,
                    markers: false
                }
            });
        }

        // Initialize smooth scrolling with Lenis
        const lenis = new Lenis({
            duration: 1.2,
            easing: (t) => Math.min(1, 1.001 - Math.pow(2, -10 * t)),
            direction: 'vertical',
            gestureDirection: 'vertical',
            smooth: true,
            smoothTouch: false,
            touchMultiplier: 2,
        });

        function raf(time) {
            lenis.raf(time);
            requestAnimationFrame(raf);
        }

        requestAnimationFrame(raf);
    </script>
</body>
</html> 